Package: mntaxa
Title: Load and format MnTaxa tables for analysis
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Amy", "Kendig", , "amy.kendig@state.mn.us", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The mntaxa R package is designed for to load and format MNTaxa tables for analysis. Users who would like to pull the most updated tables from the internal DNR database must first configure the MNTaxa ODBC DSN on their computers before using the package. External-to-DNR users can access a snapshot of MNTaxa tables included in this package. Functions included in this package allow users to select which tables to load, create a look-up table of accepted taxa, and create tables of taxonomic levels, sources/authorities, physiognomy, origin, common names, and c-values. 
